# UK date and time format

Always display dates and times in UK format via `apps/web/src/lib/datetime/uk.ts`.

- Calendar / DB `date` columns (`YYYY-MM-DD`): `formatUkDate` or `formatUkDateLong`
- Timestamps (`created_at`, etc.): `formatUkDateTime`
- E-sign / legal stamps with seconds: `formatUkDateTimeSeconds` or existing `formatEsignSignedAt`

Do **not** use:

- `toLocaleString()` / `toLocaleDateString()` without `"en-GB"`
- `toLocaleString(undefined, …)` (browser locale)
- Raw ISO strings (`2026-07-17`, `2026-07-17T20:16:00Z`) in UI copy

`<input type="date">` values stay `YYYY-MM-DD` internally; only **display** uses UK helpers.
